.TH "tomoyo_path_matches_pattern" 9 "tomoyo_path_matches_pattern" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tomoyo_path_matches_pattern \- Check whether the given filename matches the given pattern.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" tomoyo_path_matches_pattern
.BI "(const struct tomoyo_path_info *filename "  ","
.BI "const struct tomoyo_path_info *pattern "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "filename" 12
The filename to check.
.IP "pattern" 12
The pattern to compare.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns true if matches, false otherwise.

The following patterns are available.
\\     \ itself.
\ooo   Octal representation of a byte.
\*     Zero or more repetitions of characters other than '/'.
\\fI\fP     Zero or more repetitions of characters other than '/' or '.'.
\?     1 byte character other than '/'.
\$     One or more repetitions of decimal digits.
\+     1 decimal digit.
\X     One or more repetitions of hexadecimal digits.
\x     1 hexadecimal digit.
\A     One or more repetitions of alphabet characters.
\a     1 alphabet character.

\-     Subtraction operator.

/\{dir\}/   '/' + 'One or more repetitions of dir/' (e.g. /dir/ /dir/dir/
/dir/dir/dir/ ).
